                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/909: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-13T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 13, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 14—11:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>859. As an indication of the increased cooperative spirit now being displayed by
                    the Soviet authorities, I wish to report that my Naval Attaché has just returned
                    from a visit to the ports of Astrakhan and Baku where he was shown every
                    consideration and courtesy and given an opportunity to inspect Soviet naval
                    installations in those areas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
